  12.2 GHOST MODE -- THE EXCEPTION
  ----------------------------------

    Ghost Mode (Focus/Do Not Disturb mode) uses a dark purple gradient
    background ALWAYS, regardless of the system theme. This is specified in
    the existing COMPREHENSIVE-PHASE-PLAN.doc: "Dark purple gradient
    background (ALWAYS, regardless of system theme)."

    When entering Ghost Mode from light theme:
    - 0ms: Tap Ghost Mode activation
    - 0-300ms: Page background cross-fades from #F8F5FF to #0F0A1A
    - 100-400ms: Text colors cross-fade from dark to light
    - 200-500ms: Purple ambient glow appears around edges
    - 500ms+: Full Ghost Mode dark environment active
    - Exit reverses the sequence

    This transition reinforces the psychological shift -- Ghost Mode is a
    different mental space, and the visual transition signals that clearly.


  12.3 IMPLEMENTATION PRIORITY ORDER
  ------------------------------------

    Phase 2 (Core App Experience) light mode implementation order:

    WEEK 1: Foundation (must be done before any UI screens)
    1. unjynx_colors.dart -- all light mode tokens above
    2. unjynx_elevation.dart -- purple-tinted shadow system
    3. unjynx_theme.dart -- lightTheme ThemeData with M3 roles
    4. Theme toggle test -- verify all tokens switch correctly
    5. Contrast ratio unit tests -- verify all pairs meet WCAG

    WEEK 2: Core Components
    1. UnjynxTaskCard -- light mode card with hybrid strategy
    2. UnjynxGlassCard -- glass component with light/dark toggle
    3. Skeleton shimmer -- lavender shimmer configuration
    4. Bottom navigation -- glass nav bar for light mode
    5. App bar -- scrolled glass effect

    WEEK 3+: Screen-by-Screen
    Each screen implementation must verify BOTH modes.
    Widget tests: each component renders in dark AND light.
    Accessibility: each screen passes contrast checker.
    Animations: each mode has appropriate motion variants.


  12.4 TESTING REQUIREMENTS
  --------------------------

    Every light mode implementation must include:

    Unit Tests:
    - Color contrast ratios (computed mathematically) for all text/surface pairs
    - Spacing values match 8dp grid
    - Theme construction succeeds for both brightness values
    - Font weights differ between modes

    Widget Tests:
    - Each component renders correctly in Brightness.light
    - Each component renders correctly in Brightness.dark
    - Theme toggle preserves widget state
    - Glass card renders fallback when blur is disabled
    - Skeleton shimmer uses branded colors (not default gray)

    Integration Tests:
    - Full theme switch flow (Settings -> toggle -> all screens update)
    - Ghost Mode entry/exit preserves original theme
    - Reduced motion disables all animations
    - High contrast mode applies correctly
    - Bold text mode adjusts weights

    Accessibility Audit Checklist (per screen):
    - [ ] All text meets 4.5:1 contrast on its background
    - [ ] All interactive elements meet 3:1 contrast
    - [ ] Focus indicators are visible (2px+, 3:1+ contrast)
    - [ ] Color is not sole information channel
    - [ ] Touch targets are 48dp minimum
    - [ ] Animations respect reduce-motion preference


  12.5 LIGHT MODE DESIGN PRINCIPLES (UNJYNX BRAND MANIFESTO)
  ------------------------------------------------------------

    1. PURPLE MIST, NEVER WHITE.
       #F8F5FF is our canvas. It is warm, luxurious, and distinctly ours.
       No screen, no component, no surface should use #FFFFFF as a background.
       White is ONLY used for text-on-colored-surfaces and specular highlights.

    2. RESTRAINT IS LUXURY.
       In light mode, less is more. Fewer colors on screen. More whitespace.
       Subtler shadows. Lighter font weights. The brand whispers, it does
       not shout. Things 3 is our benchmark for restraint.

    3. PURPLE OWNS THE SHADOWS.
       Every shadow is rgba(26,5,51,alpha). Gray shadows (#000) are banned.
       Shadows belong to the purple ecosystem. They feel native, warm, and
       intentional -- never generic or clinical.

    4. GOLD IS EARNED, NOT GIVEN.
       #B8860B (Rich Gold) appears on CTAs, completion states, achievements,
       and progress fills. It does NOT appear casually. When gold appears, it
       means something -- an action, a milestone, a reward. This makes gold
       feel special.

    5. ANIMATIONS WALK IN THE SUN.
       Glow -> Wash. Sparkle -> Shimmer. Emission -> Border thicken. Every
       dark mode animation has a light mode counterpart that works with,
       not against, the brightness. Neither mode is an afterthought.

    6. HIERARCHY THROUGH PURPLE DEPTH.
       Surface hierarchy goes from lightest purple (background) to deepest
       purple (elevated surfaces). This creates "layers of purple glass" --
       each layer is a slightly deeper shade, building architectural depth
       without harsh borders.

    7. ACCESSIBILITY IS NON-NEGOTIABLE.
       18.5:1 text contrast is not an accident -- it is a feature. Every
       color pair, every interaction, every animation respects WCAG 2.2 AA.
       The European Accessibility Act is law. Premium means accessible.


